  "prompt": "Is the body of the Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) still untouched in his tomb in Madinah? Has anyone ever seen the body since his burial in 632?",
  "response": "According to Islamic tradition, the body of the Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) is believed to be preserved and untouched in his tomb in Medina, known as Al-Masjid an-Nabawi (the Prophet's Mosque). It is widely held among Muslims that his body was not exhumed or disturbed since his burial in 632 CE. \n\nThe tomb is located in a chamber adjacent to the mosque, which has been a significant site of pilgrimage for Muslims. However, direct access to the tomb is not permitted, and it is surrounded by a grille, making it impossible for anyone to see the body. No one has ever seen the body of the Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) since his burial, and it remains one of the important aspects of Islamic belief that his resting place is preserved in its original state.",
